The paper deals with coding theory and specifically with product codes, which are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of MDS codes, which are commonly used in coding theory and error correction (cs.CC). The paper's focus on the interaction between row and column codes during decoding suggests a connection to distributed systems (cs.DS) and possibly also to signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper's study of erasure channels suggests a connection to networking and communication (cs.NI).
